      "type": "add",
      "id": "db499721ae961b91",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "db499721ae961b91",
        "text": "Temporalization should mean here: generation of a difference of past and future. If there were only past for the system, or: if the present of the current operating were only repetition of past, the system would reproduce itself as it is. Conversely, if there were only future, the system would have to understand itself as an ongoing deviation from its own state, for example, as purpose, and it would enter into a deviation from deviation from deviation. The system gains a self-organization capable of existence and learning only if it orients itself to a difference of past and future and generates time in exactly this sense.\n"
      },
      "after": "da12808846fb7570",
